      "final_response": "Visiting Japan is wonderful any time of year, but many travelers consider **spring (late March to early May)** and **autumn (late September to early November)** to be the best seasons:\n\n- **Spring** \u2013 The iconic cherry\u2011blossom (sakura) season peaks in late March to early April in most of the country (a bit later in the north). The weather is mild, and festivals celebrating the blossoms are everywhere.\n\n- **Autumn** \u2013 From late September through November, the leaves turn brilliant shades of red, orange, and gold. Temperatures are comfortable, and you can enjoy beautiful foliage in places like Kyoto, Nikko, and the Japanese Alps.\n\nIf you prefer fewer crowds and cooler weather, **late autumn** (mid\u2011November) is especially pleasant. Winter (December\u2011February) is great for skiing in Hokkaido or the Japanese Alps, and summer (June\u2011August) offers vibrant festivals but can be hot and humid, especially in the cities.\n\nSo, depending on whether you\u2019re after cherry blossoms, colorful foliage, or winter sports, **spring and autumn are generally the most popular and scenic times to visit Japan**.",
